cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories as it deals with the pose estimation of uncooperative satellites using monocular vision-based approaches. It also involves machine learning techniques, which could place it in the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the unique challenges associated with spaceborne computer vision tasks, which could place it in the sub-category of graphics (cs.GR).
